## Requerimientos funcionales
Desarrollar un componente que permite representar los distintos sectores de barrido de una radar:

![image](data:image/png;base64,)



![image](data:image/png;base64,)


Debe permitir: 
 1. Superposición de sectores   
 2. Distinción de colores por sector 
 3. Identificar sector activo cuando selecciones ese sector     
 4. representación valores de grilla en gráfico.   
 5. representación de azimut, altura y rango   
 6. etiquetar cada uno de los sectores o targets
 7. Representación de punto.
 8. marcar una sección como activa
 9.  capturar el evento de selección de sección activa
 10. tener lineas circulares para facilitar la lectura
 11. Graficar la letra N en la parte superior de la torta.

La barra vertical no es parte del componente

## Requerimientos NO funcionales
Debe permitir captura evento de selección:

    (seccion) => { ... }

Debe recibir los siguientes parametros

    {
	    sections: [
		    {label, startAngle, endAngle, innerRadius, outerRadius, startElevation, endElevation, color, selected},
		    ...
	    ],
	    targets: [
		    {label, angle, radius, elevation, color, selected},
		    ...
	    ]
    }

### `npm run eject`

**Note: this is a one-way operation. Once you `eject`, you can't go back!**

If you aren't satisfied with the build tool and configuration choices, you can `eject` at any time. This command will remove the single build dependency from your project.

Instead, it will copy all the configuration files and the transitive dependencies (webpack, Babel, ESLint, etc) right into your project so you have full control over them. All of the commands except `eject` will still work, but they will point to the copied scripts so you can tweak them. At this point you're on your own.

You don't have to ever use `eject`. The curated feature set is suitable for small and middle deployments, and you shouldn't feel obligated to use this feature. However we understand that this tool wouldn't be useful if you couldn't customize it when you are ready for it.
